title: Add Custom Legends to leaflet Maps
text: Use addLegend*() create easily customizable legends leaflet.
code: library(leaflet) library(leaflegend) set.seed(21) data("gadmCHE") gadmCHE@data$x <- sample(c('A', 'B', 'C'), nrow(gadmCHE@data), replace = TRUE) factorPal <- colorFactor(c('#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e' , '#2ca02c'), gadmCHE@data$x) n <- 10 awesomeMarkers <- data.frame(   marker = sample(c('Font Awesome', 'Ionic', 'Glyphicon'), n, replace = TRUE),   lng = runif(n, gadmCHE@bbox[1,1], gadmCHE@bbox[1,2]),   lat = runif(n, gadmCHE@bbox[2,1], gadmCHE@bbox[2,2]) ) n2 <- 30 symbolMarkers <- data.frame(   x = runif(n2, 0, 100),   y = runif(n2, 10, 30),   lng = runif(n2, gadmCHE@bbox[1,1], gadmCHE@bbox[1,2]),   lat = runif(n2, gadmCHE@bbox[2,1], gadmCHE@bbox[2,2]) ) numericPal <- colorNumeric(hcl.colors(10, palette = 'zissou'),                            symbolMarkers$y) iconSet <- awesomeIconList(   `Font Awesome` = makeAwesomeIcon(icon = "font-awesome", library = "fa",                                    iconColor = 'rgb(192, 255, 0)',                                    markerColor = 'lightgray',                                    squareMarker = TRUE, iconRotate = 30   ),   Ionic = makeAwesomeIcon(icon = "ionic", library = "ion",                           iconColor = 'gold', markerColor = 'gray',                           squareMarker = FALSE),   Glyphicon = makeAwesomeIcon(icon = "plus-sign", library = "glyphicon",                               iconColor = '#ffffff',                               markerColor = 'black', squareMarker = FALSE) ) leaflet() |>   addTiles() |>   addPolygons(data = gadmCHE, color = ~factorPal(x), fillOpacity = .5,               opacity = 0, group = 'Polygons') |>   addLegendFactor(pal = factorPal, shape = 'polygon', fillOpacity = .5,                   opacity = 0, values = ~x, title = 'addLegendFactor',                   position = 'topright', data = gadmCHE, group = 'Polygons') |>   addAwesomeMarkers(data = awesomeMarkers, lat = ~lat, lng = ~lng,                     icon = ~iconSet[marker],                     group = 'Awesome Icons') |>   addLegendAwesomeIcon(iconSet = iconSet, title = 'addLegendAwesomeIcon',                        position = 'bottomleft',                        group = 'Awesome Icons') |>   addSymbolsSize(data = symbolMarkers, fillOpacity = .7, shape = 'plus',                  values = ~x, lat = ~lat, lng = ~lng, baseSize = 20,                  fillColor = ~numericPal(y), color = 'black',                  group = 'Symbols') |>   addLegendSize(pal = numericPal, shape = 'plus', color = 'black',                 fillColor = 'transparent', baseSize = 20, fillOpacity = .7,                 values = ~x, orientation = 'horizontal',                 title = 'addSizeLegend', position = 'bottomright',                 group = 'Symbols', data = symbolMarkers) |>   addLegendNumeric(pal = numericPal, values = ~y, title = 'addLegendNumeric',                    orientation = 'horizontal', fillOpacity = .7, width = 150,                    height = 20, position = 'bottomright', group = 'Symbols',                    data = symbolMarkers) |>   addLayersControl(overlayGroups = c('Polygons', 'Awesome Icons', 'Symbols'),                    position = 'topleft',                    options = layersControlOptions(collapsed = FALSE))

title: leaflegend 1.1.0
text: CRAN release: 2023-05-04 availableShapes provided convenience look supported symbol names. addLegendFactor, addLegendBin, addLegendQuantile now show symbol missing values exist gain naLabel argument. Label spacing adjustments addLegendNumeric support longer labels. addLegendNumeric gains argument naLabel now shows NA color missing values. addLegendNumeric gains argument labels allows user pass label names numeric breaks. breaks argument addLegendLine addLegendSize now allows user pass named list names labels. makeSymbol makeSymbolIcons can now create map symbols consistent base R pch. shape argument can accept name integer (0-indexed). availableShapes provides list named options.

title: leaflegend 1.0.0
text: CRAN release: 2022-08-05 new function addLegendSymbol added automatically encode character/factors various map symbols. default argument baseSize addLegendSize changed 20. values argument longer used addLegendBin since necessary causes problems number values less number bins. Updated example README Documentation updated makeSymbols name changed mapSymbols additional functions added . Internal functions renamed match naming conventions. Renamed makeSizeIcons makeSymbolsSize consistent naming conventions. colorValues argument removed. functionality, specify vector color fillColor. Fixed issue image styling missing raster images addLegendImage Added functions automate task creating map symbols. addSymbols create map symbols based character factor vector. addSymbolsSize create map symbols size encoding. Code re-factoring addLegendBin, addLegendQuantile, addLegendFactor grouping values different assembly HTML . Unit tests added cover current functions. Gradient IDs numeric legends now based function call data “name” values. makeSizeIcons default opacity now 1. Adding internal functions add dependencies addLegendAwesomeIcon. Awesome Icons show legends needed HTML dependencies loaded unless addAwesomeIcons included. addLegendAwesomeIcon now check dependencies “leaflet” map include missing. Added error messages invalid width, height, tickWidth, tickLength, strokeWidth arguments. Prior negative values throw errors visual output legends desirable. Ability specify values parameter formula retrieve data argument “leaflet” package. makeSymbolIcons now supports vectorization multiple shape arguments Awesome icons now centered marker addLegendAwesomeIcon adding support text parameter passed addLegendAwesomeIcon. allows svg passed icon.
